A man identified as Olakunle Obaoye, has allegedly committed suicide due to depression over his inability to pay his debts. It was gathered that the 25-year-old man was found dead inside a bush at Erinmope village, near Ayedun town in Oke-Ero Local Government Area of Kwara State. Spokesman of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, Kwara State Command, Babawale Afolabi, confirmed the incident to newsmen in Ilorin on Tuesday. CBN Crashes Rice Importation From 1.3mmt To 2,160mt In 2021 Consensus Candidacy Threatens APC February 26 Convention He said the matter has been handed over to the police for further investigations and necessary actions. He said, “On Monday 17/01/2022, one Thomas Obaoye of Ayedun town, reported to our men on ground about the demise of his brother Olakunle Obaoye (25), whose lifeless body was found hanging on the tree in what looked like a suicide.” Babawale disclosed that “operatives of the NSCDC from Ayedun Division, later went to the scene of the incident and worked together with the relatives of the deceased to bring down his corpse from the tree.”